Title: Fishy Illness
Description: Defeat Gillgut in Piscarian Fishery for Constable Kemal in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I-I don't know. If you can find out what's causing this sickness and put a stop to it, you'd save our village from collapse.\n\nIt may be something to do with the fish in the fen. My son fell ill right after he returned with a large haul.
InProgressResponse: I don't know if it's the grief over the loss of my son or the illness itself, but I have never felt so bad.\n\nI don't think I'm going to make it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You… you're back. It's done, isn't it? A few less of those foul Gillgut at the Fishery. Thank you.\n\nI hope it makes a difference, but of course, some who've eaten the fish are still fine. Who knows?

Title: Troubled Waters
Description: Defeat Ancient Guardians in South Vega Bridge and gather Ancient Herbs for Magistrate Allen in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Is there any way I can help?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Possibly. When I was new here, I heard old stories about an illness caused by the Fen itself.\n\nAfter two centuries, even my memory is hazy now, but I wonder if this same sickness has occurred before.
InProgressResponse: I feel like we're grasping at swamp reeds here, but we have to try something.\n\nAnything that can even treat the symptoms would be useful.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Yes, yes. These are the herbs I was thinking of. I'll have Alchemist Rubis look at them right away.\n\nI feel so guilty in all this. Kemal lost his son, and now he too is falling ill. Somehow, I seem to be immune.

Title: Traitorous Wraith
Description: Search for the ectoplasm trail northeast of the settlement to track down and destroy the Lost known as Mattheson the Trader. Then report back to Artificer Erasmus in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Anything that wasn't nailed down. Food, supplies, tools - people are desperate to take what they can and run. \n\nThe strange thing, though, is that some of them have become Lost - and they're still stealing from us.
InProgressResponse: Mattheson - I never fully trusted him, but I still don't think he would've been a thief when living.\n\nI just don't understand how he's maintained a sense of purpose as a Lost.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Then Mattheson has been dealt with? The traitorous bastard got what he deserved. Well done.\n\nI think he actually might have been the main culprit in all the thefts around town.

Title: Swamp Sorceress
Description: Investigate Gracewater Village and check on the wise-woman, Hazel. Then report back to Survivalist Severino in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. One of them was even a respected member of the community, long ago.\n\nHazel, the wise-woman of then Fen. A sorceress some say, she communed with the Lost. I haven't heard from her since the illness broke out.
InProgressResponse: Hazel is a wisewoman of some renown here in Weaver's Fen. \n\nI haven't visited her in some time, but everyone has a story about Hazel appearing at the right time to help or heal them.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wait… what? Hazel had fallen and become a wraith? I never would've dreamed. \n\nI suppose now she's one of those with whom she so often communed. Dear Hazel… you will be missed.

Title: Hope from the Past
Description: Defeat Ancient Guardians in North Vega Bridge searching for an Ancient Healer's Kit. Then report back to Magistrate Allen in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's what the Alchemist thinks. I hesitate to ask you to venture into the Ancient Ruins again.\n\nBut if you're willing, the Ancient Guardian Healers are on the north side of Vega Bridge. It would be a tremendous service.
InProgressResponse: If we didn’t have you and Alchemist Rubis, I might be making plans to pack up and leave myself at this point.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, praise the Ancients! Did you get the kits? This is excellent!\n\nThe herbs you retrieved before are already showing some promise. These kits may help fully alleviate the symptoms. We'll see!

Title: Payback
Description: Defeat Fenwallow Lost in Taryville for Stolen Purses for Barkeep Flores in in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Didn't run fast enough, I guess. The Lost got them out in Taryville, and now they're wandering around out there too. \n\nIn fact, if you'd help me try to get back the coin they stole, I'll reward you.
InProgressResponse: Hope you're not the squeamish sort, because you'll need to search the bodies of the Fenwallow.\n\nNasty business, but that's my entire savings!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well, look at that! My money! When I realized I had been robbed, I just about lost all hope.\n\nI know it seems petty to be so attached to some purses of coin, but I'd  been saving for sixty years!

Title: Refire the Forges
Description: Gather Metalworking Supplies in Fisher's End. Then report back to Artificer Erasmus in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Why are they harder to come by?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Because we're in a swamp! We have plenty of oil, cloth fibers, and even fish, but metal is very precious here.\n\nThat's also why keeping these forges running is so critical - but now, we have no metalworking supplies.
InProgressResponse: More than anything, I wish we could reclaim the metalworking supplies that were stolen.\n\nThey're long-gone though. Fisher's End is our best hope.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! These tools haven't seen use in years, but they'll have to do. \n\nGetting the forges up and running again is the top priority - for our iron supplies, and our sanity.

Title: Vengeance for the Lost
Description: Defeat Ancient Guardians in Canopus for Constable Kemal in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "You think he got it in the ruins?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah, I don't know… honestly, these herbs Alchemist Rubis gave me were helping, but now I feel even worse.\n\nI don't care about my own welfare, just the others. Treatments aren't enough. We need to eliminate the source.
InProgressResponse: Destroy those Ancient Guardians with extreme prejudice.\n\nIf I'm going to die, at least give me that much.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, you did it - didn't you? Gave those Boney bastards a taste of their own medicine.\n\nThat's for son, and I appreciate that you would give a sick, old man some peace this way. Here, this is yours now.

Title: The True Guardian
Description: Gather chests for Incense in Aria Village for a ceremony to honor Hazel. Then report back to Survivalist Severino in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Could Hazel's death have caused the illness?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You mean, as if the swamp itself was reacting to her passing? I... I don't know.\n\nIt's certainly a tragedy for the Fen and for all of us, but once she's become a wraith, we can't bring her back.
InProgressResponse: Hazel had a way of listening, whether it was to a person, one of the Lost, or even the Fen itself.\n\nI have a feeling this incense ritual might actually work.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You performed the incense ritual didn't you? I know you did - I could feel it. It was like a great tension was dissolved.\n\nBut you're not staying, are you? if the ritual needs to be performed regularly, who will do it?

Title: Ghosts of Weaver's Past
Description: Defeat Wraiths and Gather Chests for Music Compositions in Karburg for Constable Kemal in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Is there any way I can help?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You've honored my son's memory already, but this would be for me.\n\nLike you, my son was a person of many talents, a fisherman, a hunter, a scholar, and... a musician, a composer even. But his compositions were lost.
InProgressResponse: I think he went to Karburg because once upon a time, it was a bastion of culture here in the Fen.\n\nWe even lived there once, that was when his music was everything.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Did you find the compositions? Bless your soul, {playerName}. I can't express what this means to me. \n\nMy son's musical talent didn't come from my side, but if I survive, I will learn to play these.

Title: Reprieve for Restless Shore
Description: Speak to Innkeep Tomaso in Restless Shore to learn about the troubles there.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: All kinds of madness, from what I hear. Animals walking on two legs… factions within the Lost going to war with one another.\n\nDon't believe me? Go see for yourself -  tell Innkeep Tomaso I sent you.
InProgressResponse: I'm telling you, from what I've heard about Restless Shore, makes me grateful to live in Weaver's Fen!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've just arrived from Weaver's Fen, have you? I've heard that mysterious illness is getting better over there. \n\nSuppose that's good news, at least. Better than what we have going on here.

Title: Spores For a Cure
Description: Collect Spriggan Spores in Eridanus Caverns for Magistrate Allen in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: As a matter of fact, there is. Though it requires someone to venture into the Eridanus Caverns.\n\nTo enter that infernal maw of botanical madness, well, it's something I would normally never ask of any living soul.
InProgressResponse: Alchemist Rubis assures me that Teceros's Spores will be the final cure we've been seeking. \n\nYou have already helped us a great deal, but this will truly save our village.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The spores of the behemoth? Very… disquieting, but I'll give them to Alchemist Rubis.\n\nTHank you, {playerName}. We finally have our cure, and you can have this prize as your reward.

Title: Starting the Fire
Description: Gather strange torches from Revenants in Karburg and bring them to Torchy Cabrera in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah well, if you have not heard anything, then perhaps it is best we keep it that way.\n\nSuffice to say that I am no longer welcome in the Restless Shore settlement. It's really because of my research.
InProgressResponse: Look for the ones holding the torches. And try not to get burned too badly.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, yes. Don't you see? The light, the color… it is truly beautiful. \n\nI will study these and see if I might discover how they burn so long and so bright.

Title: Burning from the Inside
Description: Collect Perpetual Illumination Essences from Ancients at Aqua Acadia and bring them to Torchy Cabrera in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I believe the Ancients knew the secrets of eternal fire and eternal light as well.\n\nHave you ever noticed the perpetual glow that clings to the walking corpses of the Ancient Guardians?
InProgressResponse: Amid the ruins of Aqua Acadia to the north, you will see for yourself.\n\nThe Guardians there glow more than anywhere else. Gather their essence, my friend.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Perfect… perfect! This illumination essence is the missing link!\n\nCombined with the substance in the torches from Karburg, I feel certain we have found the secret!

Title: Hellfire & Brimstone Oven
Description: Travel to Navarro's Kitchen and defeat Chef Navarro and collect "Navarro's Flaming Duck Recipe". Then bring it to Torchy in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You must help me clear my name so I can go home. You see, I was exiled from the settlement for starting a fire...\n\nBut for once, it was NOT me who ignited the flame. I was framed, you see!
InProgressResponse: Chef Navarro's Kitchen is not far, and I feel certain he still carries his 'Flaming Duck Recipe.'\n\nDefeat the bastard and get the recipe and I can finally clear my name.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: He still had it, didn't he? Yes… yes! This proves that HE was the one who started the fire! \n\nThank you, my friend! I cannot thank you enough for helping me get back home.

Title: (Elite) Fenton's Fiend
Description: Travel to Fenton's Hamlet, slay the Fenton Ravager, and bring back proof of its demise to Evelyn Van Heck in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I expected as much. Blast.\n\nMy companions and I formed a band called The White Skulls. We hunt the many monsters of Aeternum in exchange for coin. We were chasing a bounty when my companions and I were slain.
InProgressResponse: Just so we are clear, I am not responsible if the Ravager kills you as well. You take on this bounty at your own risk. I am content to wait here for my company to return.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: No sign of the others yet, but at least there's one less monster for this beleaguered fen to deal with. \n\nHere. Your bounty, as promised.

Title: (Elite) Keeping the Faith
Description: Travel to Periville and find Joan and Markus. Then report back to Evelyn Van Heck in Weaver's Fen.
PlayerPrompt: “What do you think happened to them?”
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The obvious, or they probably went on to our next bounty to get rich without me. That would be something Joan and Markus would do. It certainly wouldn’t be the first time, anyway. \n\nCall me soft, but…
InProgressResponse: Hope for the best, prepare for… well, I would rather not think about that.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I am at a loss for words, traveler.\n\nThis emblem defines us. Joan carved them herself.

Title: (Elite) Extreme Exorcism
Description: Travel to Karburg, slay Ruiz Velazquez, and collect proof of his demise for Evelyn Van Heck in Weaver's Fen.
PlayerPrompt: “Do you want me to find him, too?”
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. You have already risked so much. At least… finding Ruiz will be a little easier. I know where he would have arisen. It is sad, but at least there is comfort in certainty.
InProgressResponse: I hope I am wrong. I do not think I am, but where there is hope, there is also the potential for disappointment. Too much, and we lose ourselves. Just like they did.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Am I really the only one of my company left? Ruiz and I had such plans. So much we intended to do, together. Now he and the others have become the monsters we fought so hard to put down.

Title: Gators Gone Wild
Description: Collect alligator scales from Gators in Weaver's Fen and return them to Hunter Samuel in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: A hunt, of course! You and I shall venture forth into the marshes in pursuit of the most ferocious, cunning, and formidable beasts this festering land has to offer!\n\nJust as my forebears have done since time immemorial!
InProgressResponse: I shall make my own way into the stinking bog.\n\nYou go on ahead. I suspect you will need the head start, after all.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, you have returned! I was beginning to wonder. Now, let me see your trophies. \n\nYes... thick, unblemished, and as hard as anything. These are certifiably the remains of several fine beasts. Well done!

Title: No Mere Pigs
Description: Collect boar tusks from Polder Boars in Weaver's Fen and return them to Hunter Samuel just south of the settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Boars! No ordinary boars, but boars the size of three men! We will not waste our skill on mere pigs!\n\nBring me the largest tusks you can find, and we shall compare trophies. They're a plague to this region!
InProgressResponse: Ah, yes, I shall be along promptly! \n\nUh, once I have finished oiling my musket, of course.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The prodigal hunter returns! You truly are a fellow after my own heart. Let us see your fine trophies. Hand them over, I say!

Title: The True Contest
Description: Collect wolf paws from Mallory Wolves, found north of Fenton's Hamlet, and return them to Hunter Samuel in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: How can you have won if there has been no contest? Nay, we shall have to settle this once and for all.
InProgressResponse: I relish the end of our contest. Go on. I am right behind you!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You are simply not going to believe this. My musket was ready, my boots laced, my satchel patched, and a COURIER found me on the road! There was urgent business in the hamlet to attend to.\n\nAlas, I must concede.

Title: Stalk of Shame
Description: Defeat the Werna Packleader at Dusty Paw Burrow, far to the north and west of Weaver’s Fen Hamlet, and collect a trophy from your kill for Hunter Samuel in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Do you know what it's like, being saddled with a legacy like mine? Why, if people only knew how incompetent I really am, my family name would be utterly ruined. \n\nThat is why I need your help.
InProgressResponse: I will not pretend that this arrangement pleases me, my friend, but I am grateful that you have chosen to take pity on me.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, well, there it is. She was enormous, wasn’t she? I, uh, I wish I could have seen it myself. \n\nAs promised, here is your bounty. And a tip. Your… continuing discretion is appreciated.

Title: Story of the Stones
Description: Gather stone samples from rubble in the nearby ruins. Then report back to Architect Na Li in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, exactly! These stones have been here as long as anyone can remember. If we can learn how the Ancient architects reinforced these structures, imagine what WE could accomplish!\n\nSo, I have a theory!
InProgressResponse: Do you have those stone samples for me? They are vital to my research.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look at this beautiful basalt you’ve brought me. I wonder where the Ancients sourced it from?\n\nNow, let’s see about that aging… huh. Wait…that can’t be right.

Title: Spanning the Ages
Description: Gather stone samples from rubble at South Vega Bridge. Then report back to Architect Na Li in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I need another sample from a newer site to be certain. Master Ting Long once theorized that the bridge that spans the marshes was built in a more recent era. \n\nCould you bring me samples from South Vega Bridge for comparison?
InProgressResponse: I hope to have answers for us soon, my friend. And if I am right, then we might see some NEW wonders in Aeternum.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Great, you’re back. Let’s take a look at these new samples you've found.\n\nInteresting… these are less weathered, but only just. Fascinating.

Title: Deep Time
Description: Gather stone samples from rubble at Andrometus. Then report back to Architect Na Li in Weaver's Fen.
PlayerPrompt: "Wouldn't that mean the Ancients are also that old?”
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It does, doesn’t it? So many questions, but we must resist the temptation to draw conclusions. Stone dating is far from an established field of study, after all.\n\nRegardless, I am looking toward the future, today.
InProgressResponse: Let me know when you've got those Andrometus samples. I have some theories about how they accomplished these feats of longevity, but I never draw conclusions without proof.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You and I will be friends, after this. Perhaps I will carve your name into the aqueducts of the future. Or would you prefer a temple? Maybe a stone garden?\n\nI am certain I can extract their secrets, thanks to you.

Title: That Beautiful Stench
Description: Gather materials in Weaver's Fen and then visit an arcane repository to craft a perfume for Tullius Volusus in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, precisely! That scent, it is primal, inescapable. It reaches down through your nose, through your lungs, into your very soul. With every breath, it commands, "Be awake! Be alive!”
InProgressResponse: Can the unique fragrance of Weaver’s Fen truly be replicated by human hands? I await your return with bated breath.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hmm, yes…decadent, musky, with a sulfuric accord that resonates right through to the top notes…you’ve captured Weaver's Fen perfectly. \n\nYou may be a genius, my friend! Ah, my eyes are watering with emotion!

Title: Misplaced Treasure
Description: Search chests at North Vega Bridge for a clue to Nora’s whereabouts. Then report back to Leonie Roggeveen in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Likewise. I was wondering if you might be able to help me? \n\nYou see, Nora and I like to play a little game to pass the time. She hides herself and leaves clues for me to find amongst these relics. Brain teasers, and the like.
InProgressResponse: This game was much less stressful when it took place in EMPTY ruins, you see. I do hope she's alright.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You’re back! And in one piece! Do you have the clue? It could be a coin, a note, an etching…\n\nOh, give it here. The suspense is killing me.

Title: Following Nora
Description: Search chests at Canopus for a clue to Nora’s whereabouts. Then report back to Leonie Roggeveen in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Something about the iconography she used… It suggests half of a whole. Aha!\n\nShe means to have me combine two clues to find her, but this tells me the second clue is at Canopus. Very clever. Care to help again?
InProgressResponse: As thrilled as I am, her long absence is truly starting to wear on me. Could you hurry with that clue? It would put me at ease to finally find her.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Another coin! Wonderful, hand it over, let’s see what she has to say…

Title: Odds in Her Favor
Description: Follow Nora's trail to Aqua Acadia and search chests for the final clue.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Nora thought she could stump me, did she? Me, the greatest coin collector in Aeternum? Come on, give me a tough one, ha!
InProgressResponse: Hopefully we near the end of our chase, my friend. Nora can handle herself… right?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I see you found my note. Did Dr. Leonie send you?

Title: Nora, Found
Description: Return to Dr. Leonie Roggeveen in Weaver's Fen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yeah, no wonder. When those Guardians appeared, the only two things I could think about were "I'm going to die" and "Leonie will be so worried".
InProgressResponse: I'll meet you and Leonie back on the road. I'll sneak out while you're distracting them.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You’re back! Nora told me everything. I am SO relieved.\n\nI’m going to have a talk with her about taking some precautions next time. But this was a fine game, and you were an enormous help. Thank you!

Title: Protective Wyrd
Description: Recover the components and recipes needed to assemble the armor Protective Wyrd. Then report back to Survivalist Severino in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There is always more we could do, which is why I have a gift for you.\n\nHazel once spoke of a set of armor said to keep its wearer protected against the worst sort of fates.
InProgressResponse: Nothing is truly lost on Aeternum, or so I tell myself.\n\nWhen the time is right, you will find what you need to craft the Protective Wyrd, I know you will.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: There's something about you... Oh! You found everything you needed!\n\nThis is the most impressive attire I've ever laid eyes on. I can feel the power of the Protective Wyrd from here.

Title: Step in the Right Direction
Description: Collect Hallowed Fabric from Fenton Hamlet, Essence of Undeath from Cutthroat Cavern, and Purified Pitch from Jetsam Isle. Then visit a Tier 3 Outfitting Station to craft the Protected Wyrd Shoes.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @1303_1311_01_Shoes_Proposal
InProgressResponse: @1303_1311_01_Shoes_Incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1303_1311_01_Shoes_Complete

Title: Wrapped in Wards
Description: Collect Neptunian Buckles from Neptune's Fury, Consecrated Thread from Solitude Cemetery, and Ancient Armor Scraps from Gelida Pillars. Then visit a Tier 3 Outfitting Station to craft the Protected Wyrd Shirt.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @1303_1311_02_Shirt_Proposal
InProgressResponse: @1303_1311_02_Shirt_Incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1303_1311_02_Shirt_Complete

Title: Predestined Perils
Description: Collect Stitched Wards from Eeriedune Graveyard, Ceremonial Worked Wool from Eridanus, and Infused Lining from Lunaryth. Then visit a Tier 3 Outfitting Station to craft the Protected Wyrd Pants.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @1303_1311_03_Pants_Proposal
InProgressResponse: @1303_1311_03_Pants_Incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1303_1311_03_Pants_Complete

Title: Within Fate's Grasp
Description: Collect Cragview Reinforced Weave from Cragview, Wyrdwood Charms from Blisteroot, and Shambhala Cleansed Fibers from Shambhala. Then visit a Tier 3 Outfitting Station to craft the Protected Wyrd Gloves.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @1303_1311_04_Gloves_Proposal
InProgressResponse: @1303_1311_04_Gloves_Incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1303_1311_04_Gloves_Complete

Title: Facing Destiny
Description: Collect Dawnglow Omens from Pavo, Virid Resin from Bramblecliff, and Spectral Cloth from Upper Slag Mine. Then visit a Tier 3 Outfitting Station to craft the Protected Wyrd Hat.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @1303_1311_05_Hat_Proposal
InProgressResponse: @1303_1311_05_Hat_Incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @1303_1311_05_Hat_Complete

Title: Tracking the Huntress
Description: Acquire Ancient Wood from Rafflesia, Wyrdwood Resin from Verdant Ascent, Hawk Feather from Propus, and a Lucky Rabbit's Foot from Echowhine Hollow to craft the bow known as "The Huntress." Then report back to Barkeep Flores in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Wouldn't you, though? It'll be up to you to do all the leg work.\n\nIf you can collect all the materials on the list, I think this bow - "the Huntress" - will be the envy of everyone in town. Good luck!
InProgressResponse: Ah, still tracking down the Huntress, are you?\n\nIt'll take some time, I reckon.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look at you - fresh in from the wilds and now a legendary tracker, at least to my mind. Finding all the materials can't have been easy. \n\nBut the Huntress - she'll take good care of you. Keep your quiver full out there.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Huntress
Description: She hides among the trees. Among the redwoods, she is truly at home.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Huntress
Description: The resin of the tree perfumes the air. If you're all alone, yet notice that scent, beware.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Huntress
Description: With eyes like the hawk, she sees for miles. Her vision is clear.

Title: Collect items then craft the Huntress
Description: She closes upon her prey, and slowly pulls back. The freedom she feels is like that of an arrow.

Title: Falmea's Wrath
Description: Acquire Singed Branches from Amphus, Wyrdwood Ashes from Fornax, Unhallowed Water from Neptune's Fury, and the Heart of All Flame from New Balefire to craft the Fire Staff called "Falmea's Wrath." Then report back to Artificer Erasmus in the Weaver's Fen Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Perfect. I've been working on a schematic for some time - I call it "Falmea's Wrath."\n\nIf you can acquire all the necessary elements, this will staff will make you a true master of the flame. Good luck.
InProgressResponse: Still hunting for the elements to make "Falmea's Wrath"?\n\nKeep at it - I think you'll find it a worth investment.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, behold! Your diligence has paid off - you must've had to trek all over Aeternum!\n\nBut now, you enjoy the benefits! Falmea's Wrath! A finer staff has never been crafted! Wield it with pride, {playerName}.

Title: Collect items used to craft Falmea's Wrath
Description: Falmea burned the Wyrdwood into the air, and left the air hanging with great sorrow.

Title: Collect items used to craft Falmea's Wrath
Description: Falmea let ashes from the Wyrdwood fall. A pure white on the ground, felled.

Title: Collect items used to craft Falmea's Wrath
Description: Falmea revealed her unhallowed water and sprinkled it into the ash.

Title: Collect items then craft Falmea's Wrath
Description: Falmea spoke the unspeakable and, from a tornado of flame, retrieved a staff.
